**IRPA:34**
**IRPA:34(1)** The Minister may, in accordance with the regulations, declare that a foreign national is inadmissible on grounds of
**IRPA:34(1)** seriousness of crime
**IRPA:34(1)(a)** on the basis that they have been convicted in Canada of an offence under an Act of Parliament punishable by way of indictment, or of two or more offences under any Act of Parliament that, in aggregate, make up a term of imprisonment of at least two years;
**IRPA:34(1)(b)** on the basis that they have been convicted of an offence outside Canada that, if committed in Canada, would constitute an offence under an Act of Parliament punishable by way of indictment, or of two or more such offences that, in aggregate, make up a term of imprisonment of at least two years;
**IRPA:34(1)(b)(c)** of constituting a danger to the public in Canada or for being likely to engage in serious criminal activity.
**IRPA:34(2)** The Minister may, in accordance with the regulations, declare that a foreign national is inadmissible on the basis of
**IRPA:34(2)(a)** organized criminal activity;
